<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="113" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1626,1941]" pageId="1" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1842,1868]" pageId="1" pageNumber="113">Etymology.</emphasis>
The genus name 
<emphasis box="[538,597,1843,1868]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="113">Miri-</emphasis>
is for English word 
<emphasis box="[835,961,1842,1868]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="113">miraculous</emphasis>
. It is used to emphasize the amazing discovery of this genus/species in such a high altitude from 
<collectingRegion box="[797,900,1878,1904]" country="China" name="Zhejiang" pageId="1" pageNumber="113">Zhejiang</collectingRegion>
, where are covered by snow from December to March the next year.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
